fix: improve lounge zone visibility in dark mode

Fixed critical visibility issues where agents and furniture appeared as very
dark black objects in the lounge zone, making them nearly invisible against
the dark lounge background (#231e33).

Key improvements:
• AgentAvatar.tsx:
  - Avatar background: #1e293b → #3f3f46 (lighter zinc, improved contrast)
  - Sub-agent badge: #1e293b → #3f3f46 (same improvement)
  - Added dark mode visibility halo: Semi-transparent status color ring around
    agents in dark mode for enhanced visibility and visual separation from
    background

• Sofa.tsx (lounge furniture):
  - Cushion: #1e293b → #ea580c (dark orange, highly visible)
  - Frame: #0f172a → #d97706 (warm brown, matches aesthetic and visibility)
  - Accent: #f97316 → #fbbf24 (lighter orange for detail visibility)
  - Result: Sofas are now clearly visible decorative elements in dark mode

Before: Agents and furniture blended into dark lounge background, making the
zone appear empty or hard to navigate.

After: Clear visual separation with improved contrast. Agents stand out with
visibility halo effect. Furniture is warm orange and easy to identify. Working
states remain clearly visible with status color indicators.

TypeScript: ✓ (no errors)
